## 🤝 Contributing to DogBot
Thank you for your interest in helping improve DogBot!
DogBot is an open-source project with one goal: to understand dog behavior in an empathetic and intelligent way – powered by GPT and Weaviate.

## 🧠 What is DogBot?
DogBot is currently organized into three repositories:
- dogbot-ui: The frontend interface
- dogbot-agent: The GPT & Weaviate-powered backend agent
- dogbot-ops: Curated content, JSON data, and Weaviate schemas

### 🚀 How to Contribute
## 1. Fork & Pull Request
Fork the relevant repo
Create a new branch (feature/xyz, fix/abc, etc.)
Keep your code clean and well-documented
Open a pull request with a short, clear description

## 2. Local Setup
UI (React)
bash
Kopieren
Bearbeiten
cd dogbot-ui
npm install
npm start

## Agent (FastAPI & Weaviate)
cd dogbot-agent
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn main:app --reload

## 3. Style Guide
Write clean, readable code
Comment complex logic where needed
Never commit API keys or sensitive information

### 💬 Questions & Collaboration
The best way to ask questions or suggest improvements is via GitHub Issues in the relevant repository.

Thanks for being part of the pack! 🐾